00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:23,824
Welcome to Telugu Ruchi! On this channel, we show you various flavored rice recipes like biryani, pulao, fried rice, khichdi, and more. Today, let’s look at a traditional and tasty one.

2
00:00:23,824 --> 00:00:53,034
Today, we’ll see how to make flavorful Thalassery Chicken Biryani. For the masala: 10g cinnamon, 5g cloves, 10g cardamom, 10g pepper, 5g black cumin, 5g fennel, 5g star anise.

3
00:00:53,034 --> 00:01:14,686
[No transcript; assumed silence or background action]

4
00:01:14,686 --> 00:01:43,575
Also add: 15g cashews, 15g raisins, 75g onions, salt to taste, 2 bay leaves, 5g turmeric, half kg chicken, enough water, 50g tomatoes, 50g shallots.

5
00:01:43,575 --> 00:02:11,960
75g curd, hot water as needed, 10ml oil, ½ kg Jeera Samba rice, 1g saffron, ghee as needed, 10ml lemon juice. To start, heat a pan and dry roast the cinnamon and cloves.

6
00:02:13,444 --> 00:02:41,355
Add black cumin, fennel, star anise and roast lightly. Then add poppy seeds and roast briefly. Transfer to a plate and let cool.

7
00:02:44,663 --> 00:02:58,129
Grind into a fine powder and set aside.

8
00:03:13,942 --> 00:03:37,955
In the same pan, add ginger, garlic, green chili, coriander, mint, and salt. Grind it into a smooth paste and keep it aside.

9
00:04:08,683 --> 00:04:38,603
In a clay pot, heat ghee. Fry the cashews and raisins, and set them aside. Then fry onions.

10
00:04:54,144 --> 00:05:19,694
Add bay leaves and turmeric. Then add the earlier ground chicken masala paste.

11
00:05:40,247 --> 00:06:06,370
Add chopped tomatoes, mix well, cover and cook for 15 minutes. Then add the chopped shallots.

12
00:06:09,391 --> 00:06:31,733
Add the fried onions, the masala powder we made earlier, and curd. Mix thoroughly.

13
00:06:37,858 --> 00:07:06,665
Cover and cook for 5 minutes, then set aside. In another clay pot, boil water with black cumin, salt, and oil.

14
00:07:09,668 --> 00:07:34,120
Add Jeera Samba rice. Cook till 70% done. Drain the rice completely.

15
00:07:56,733 --> 00:08:26,281
Layer the cooked chicken masala at the bottom. Add lemon juice, saffron water, ghee. Cover and cook on dum (steam) for 15 minutes.

16
00:08:28,576 --> 00:08:56,976
Finally, garnish with the fried cashews, raisins, coriander, and onions. The delicious Thalassery Chicken Biryani is ready!

